<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3825] Allow users to specify different types of state stores in Streams DSL</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3825</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Today the high-level Streams DSL uses hard-coded types of state stores (i.e. persistent RocksDB) for their stateful operations. But for advanced users they should be able to specify different types of state stores (in-memory, persistent, customized) also in the DSL, instead of resorting to the lower-level APIs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12977883">KAFKA-3825</key>
